Standalone JIRA should be easily (e.g. with the help of a GUI-frontend) configured to use SSL and/or require client-side certificates. These certificates should be created and managed by JIRA itself (no need to search the internet for documentation about how to do it!). When client-side certificates are active, the user should (optionally) be automatically logged in - no need for a separate user/password login.

This is a must-have feature for us, because we want to connect our JIRA server with the internet, but do not want the world to hack into it.

